MULTI-TALENTED comedian, Tolulope Olayiwola aka MC Remote has admitted that comedy changed his life for the best. The comic act also stated that his kids can inherit his God-given talent. The funnyman revealed this to The Nation in a recent chat while recounting how comedy has put food on his table.   Anyiam-Osigwe to chair Federation of Nollywood Guilds     Ayinla Kolington worried about lyrical contents	     Mide Martins: Filmmaking is more than making money   He said, “My children can inherit this talent. Comedy is what has helped me so far, it has been bringing food, it has changed my life, I cannot joke with it, if I see someone coming up saying he wants to pursue this dream, I will not discourage that person.” With over 500 thousand followers on Instagram, Remote who is also known as Pastor Remote because of his funny gospel skits noted that he is from a mixed background both Christain and Muslim. The Ibadan Polytechnic graduate, who joined the comedy industry in 2014, also narrated how his journey into the world of skitmaking and comedy began. Speaking on challenges he faced as a rising comedian, he said “one of them I faced earlier was when I attended shows, I become scared of the audience because probably it was my first performance there (in a new environment) and then because of anxiety it might make one not deliver well and all. That was the challenge I faced coming up but I have been able to overcome it”.